casebody.data:
William N. Pooley, Respondent v. Mendez D. Senior, Appellant. Decided January 11, 1892. Motion by plaintiff at the general term to vacate order of the general term entered October 10, 1891.

Before Freedman, P. J., McAdam and Gildersleeve, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Motion granted, with $10 costs of motion to be paid by defendant’s attorney, personally.
